  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Time to 99% Inhibition of Serum Thromboxane</measure>
    <time_frame>11 days</time_frame>
    <description>Serial measurements of aspirin anti-platelet activity will be collected over 11 days, and compared between groups, to allow a determination of pharmacodynamic (anti-platelet) bioequivalence between study drugs. Aspirin's antiplatelet activity is measured by the capacity of platelets to generate serum thromboxane (a surrogate marker for inhibition of COX-1 by aspirin). Inhibition of serum thromboxane is a key marker of antiplatelet efficacy.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
